Predators Beat Canucks 4-3 to Avoid Elimination in NHL Conference Playoffs

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-05-08T04:02:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/predators-beat-canucks-4-3-to-avoid-elimination-in-nhl-conference-playoffs.html
David Legwand and Joel Ward each
scored two goals to help the  Nashville Predators  defeat the
 Vancouver  Canucks 4-3 and avoid elimination in the National
Hockey League Stanley Cup playoffs.  Legwand had goals in the first and second period to tie the
score at 2-2, while Ward added two more in the third for the win
at Rogers Arena in Vancouver.  Raffi Torres had a goal and Ryan Kesler scored two for the
top-seeded Canucks in the Western Conference semifinals.  The Predators trail the Canucks 3-2 in the best-of-seven
series, which moves to Nashville for Game 6 tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  